tags: v excited for what y'all put in the comments
title: my favourite youtubers with tourettes
body:
by the way, happy tourette syndrome awareness month! TS awareness month is from may 15 to june 15 (in america, at least)

I have put warnings on some of these youtubers if they have swearing, self harming, or overall severe tics so that people with echolalia/echopraxia don’t accidentally pick them up.

  • Jamie sanders- posts about life with TS and dispelling common stereotypes. has done a collab video with @tourettestoucan !
  • TourettesTeen- posts challenges with tourettes that most people without it wouldn’t think about (tourettes vs. egg, tourettes vs. jenga) and overall a great channel. her tics are very severe so if you have echo tics you might want to be careful.
  • Any video from Jess thom- unfortunately I don’t think she has a youtube channel but she’s just so wonderful she should definitely be on this list. She has multiple ted talks, she has her own show (backstage in biscuitland) and is an amazing advocate for tourettes. she has some self harmful tics so if you have echopraxia tics you might want to be careful.
  • Adam ladell (formerly Tictwitchteen)- a singer with TS, ADHD, and OCD. Unfortunately he doesn’t post much anymore. He has swearing and shouting tics so if you have echo tics you may want to be careful.
  • Melody Little- She posts about Tourette’s and parenting with tourette’s. she has swearing tics so people with echo tics may want to be careful.
  • idranktheseawater ( @melissacwater)- posts about Tourette’s syndrome and mental health, like eating disorders, depression, and related conditions. She has swearing tics so people with echo tics may want to be careful.
  • Rowan Kitterman ( @castiel-has-the-fonebox )- posts about Tourette’s syndrome, being lgbt+ and anything else going on in his life.

Please add your favourite youtubers with TS to the notes!
